title: Raptors assign Jared Sullinger to Raptors 905 on rehab assignment
text:
Presented by: Raptors assign Jared Sullinger to Raptors 905 on rehab assignment 
Toronto Raptors forward Jared Sullinger has been assigned to the Raptors 905, the team's D-League affiliate, on a rehab assignment (Chris Young/CP) Steven Loung January 28, 2017, 6:12 PM Steven Loung January 28, 2017, 6:12 PM 
Toronto Raptors forward Jared Sullinger has been assigned to the Raptors 905, the team’s D-League affiliate, on a rehab assignment. 
He will be in Mississauga Saturday night when the 905 take on the Delaware 87ers. . @Raptors assign Jared Sullinger to @Raptors905 on rehab assignment. He will be active for tonight's game vs. Delaware at Hershey Centre. 
— Raptors905MR (@Raptors905MR) January 28, 2017 
Sullinger recently returned from a foot injury that sidelined him for the first 41 games of the Raptors’ season. The 24-year-old has struggled since being re-activated, averaging a measly 4.0 points and 2.6 rebounds on 25.8 per cent shooting in 14.0 minutes per game. 
The Raptors had lost five straight games with Sullinger in the lineup, but ended up snapping the slide on Friday against the Milwaukee Bucks with Sullinger listed as a DNP-CD. 
This will mark the first time in the five-year veteran's career that he will play in a D-League game. More from Sportsnet
